cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category as the paper discusses combining logics and proposes a new category of diagrammatic logics. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper mentions studying computational side-effects during the execution of an imperative program. 
3. cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible sub-category as the paper discusses the evolution of state during program execution. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible sub-category as the paper may discuss the use of categorical constructions for combining diagrammatic logics in the context of data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a less likely sub-category, but still possible as the paper discusses the evolution of state during program execution and the study of computational side-effects.
